description:
You are a satellite operations engineer performing a Mission Readiness Review (MRR). One mandatory checklist item is independent verification that the ground system's command and telemetry dictionary matches the mission's Interface Control Document (ICD). Programmatically query the complete command and telemetry dictionary for the 'INST' target in OpenC3 COSMOS and produce a structured JSON dictionary file at /home/ga/Desktop/cmd_tlm_dictionary.json. The file must document all telemetry packet names with their constituent item names (minimum 3 packets), all command names with their parameter names (minimum 3 commands), and a summary section with aggregate counts.

Required JSON format:
{
  "target": "INST",
  "telemetry_packets": {
    "<PACKET_NAME>": {
